<center>
   <br><br>
   <h1>Expressions</h1>
   <br>
</center>
<font size=4>
<ul>
   <li>Expressions are Java language expressions whose value is evaluated
and returned to the page as a string.</li>
   <li>These were created due to the fact that using scriptlets to always
write to a page can become cumbersome having to use multiple
out.println() statements.</li>
</ul>
<br><br>
<p>Example of an expression:</p>
<font color="red">
   <p>The current date is:
      <br>&lt%= new java.util.Date() %></p>
</font>
</font>
